{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀπόδειξις</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> -δεξις, εως, ἡ, (ἀποδείκνυμι) <b>showing forth, making</b> <b>known, exhibiting,</b> δι᾽ ἀπειροσύνην.. κοὐκ ἀπόδειξιν τῶν ὑπὸ γαίας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 196. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>setting forth, publication,</b> Ἠροδότου.. ἱστορίης ἀπόδεξις[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>Prooem.;</b> ἀρχῆς ἀ. <b>an exposition, sketch</b> of it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.97; ἀ. περὶ τὸν πολιτικόν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 277a; περί τινος “R.” 358b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>proof,</b> βουλομένοισί σφι γένοιτ᾽ ἂν ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.101; ἀ. ποιεῖσθαι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 12.19, etc.; especially by words, ἀποδείξεις εὑρίσκειν τινός 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 10.3; ἀ. λέγειν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 162e; -ξεις φέρειν 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 12.5.5\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χρῆσθαί τινι ἀποδείξει τινός use it <b>as a proof</b> of a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.160a\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, <b>proofs,</b> or <b>arguments in proof</b> of, τινός[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.300, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 73a; λέγειν τι ἐς ἀπόδειξιν τοῦ περιέσεσθαι τῷ πολέμῳ 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.13; ἄνευ ἀποδείξεως 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 92d; μετ᾽ ἀ. 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.1.3, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. λαμβάνειν.. τῶν μανθανόντων <b>test</b> them by examination, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.736d; ἀ. ποιεῖσθαι τῶν ἐφήβων “IG” 2.470.40; ἀ. τέχνης \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<b>specimen,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Dionysius Comicus 3.4; ἀ. αὑτοῖς δοῦναί τινος 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.79f, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>citation,</b> ποιητῶν καὶ ἱστοριαγράφων ἀποδείξεις[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 685.93 (Crete, 2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__3.b</b></Level4> in the Logic of [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], <b>demonstration,</b> i. e. <b>deductive proof by syllogism,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anthologia Graeca 0.71b17, +others, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 1p.25U., “Stoicorum Veterum Fragmenta” 2.89\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to inductive proof (ἐπαγωγή), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Anthologia Graeca” 0.81a40:—sometimes in a loose sense, ἀ. ῥητορικὴ ἐνθύμημα [prev. author] “Rh.” 1355a6. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>appointment,</b> θεωρῶν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 402.29 (Delph., 3rd c.BC). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> (from <i>middle</i>) ἀ. ἔργων μεγάλων <b>display, achievement</b> of mighty works, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.207, compare 2.101, 148.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0585","accentedUnicode":"ἀπόδειξις","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0575","matchingForm":"ἀπό","stepTransliteration":"apo","gloss":"away from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G0584","matchingForm":"ἀποδείκνυμι","stepTransliteration":"apodeiknumi","gloss":"to display","_zh_tw_Gloss":"證實","_es_Gloss":"dar a conocer","_zh_Gloss":"证实"},{"strongNumber":"G1166","matchingForm":"δεικνύω","stepTransliteration":"deiknuō","gloss":"to show","_zh_tw_Gloss":"指示","_es_Gloss":"mostrar ","_zh_Gloss":"指示"}],"sho